ACS on Vehicle Full Speed Moving
ACS on Vehicle Full Speed Traversing
ACS on Turret Full Speed Traversing

The maximum health of the ammo rack. If this value drops down to less than its corresponding regenerated health value, the reloading time will be increased by 100 %. If this value reaches zero and there are shells on the ammo rack, a sympathetic detonation will occur and the tank will explode immediately.
The traverse speed of the chassis.
The maximum maintainable forward speed of the vehicle.
The maximum maintainable reverse speed of the vehicle.
The resistance factor applied while the vehicle is moving or traversing on hard terrains (roads, pavement and cobblestones).
The resistance factor applied while the vehicle is moving or traversing on medium terrains (some paths, dirt, sand, grass and shallow water).
The resistance factor applied while the vehicle is moving or traversing on soft terrains (swamps and deep water).
Whether the chassis can traverse on the spot without moving forwards or backwards.
The braking power of the vehicle.
The maximum angle to which the vehicle can climb.
The unit spread factor applied to the aiming-circle while the vehicle is moving.
The spread factor applied to the aiming-circle while the vehicle is moving in full speed.
The unit spread factor applied to the aiming-circle while the vehicle is traversing.
The spread factor applied to the aiming-circle while the vehicle is traversing in full speed.
The maximum load of the suspension.

The maximum health of the tracks. If this value reaches zero, the tracks will be broken so the vehicle cannot move or traverse. However, a damaged chassis does not affect the mobility of the vehicle. Both tracks have its own health pool.
The effective output power of the engine.
The power of engine divided by the weight of the vehicle, reflects the vehicle's acceleration performance.
Chance of the engine will catch fire while being hit.

The maximum health of the engine. If this value drops down to less than its corresponding regenerated health value, the vehicle would move and traverse 50 % slower. If this value reaches zero, the engine will be broken so the vehicle cannot move or traverse.
The maximum health of the fuel tank. If this value reaches zero, the tank will catch fire.
The type of fuel stored in this fuel tank.
The reload time of the gun. For a auto-loading gun, this is the time needed to reload the entire magazine.

The accuracy of the gun, roughly the minimum radius of the aiming circle back-projected to 100 metres away from the gun. To be exact, this value describes three standard deviations σ in a normal distribute, from the centre of your aim.
The aiming time of the gun, represented by the time needed for the aiming circle to shrink to its 1/e (roughly one thirds) size.
Represents how many shells could fire within one minute.
Maximum angle the gun could elevate.
Maximum angle the gun could depress.
The spread factor applied to the aiming-circle after the gun fires.
The unit spread factor applied to the aiming-circle while the turret is traversing.
The spread factor applied to the aiming-circle while the turret is traversing in full speed.
The spread factor applied to the aiming-circle while the gun is damaged.
The horizontal traverse range of the gun.
The maximum traverse speed of the gun while moving within its traverse range.
The ammunition capacity of the tank.
The ammunition capacity of a stripper clip.
The reload time of the stripper clip.
Number of shells could be fired in one shot.
Represents how many shells could be fire within one minute, if stripper clip reloading is not needed.

The maximum health of the gun. If this value drops down to less than its corresponding regenerated health value, the size of the aiming circle will be enlarged by 100 %. If this value reaches zero, the gun will be broken and cannot shoot.
The primary frontal armour of the hull.
The primary side armour of the hull.
The primary rear armour of the hull.
The maximum health of the hull, which will be added up to the maximum health of the tank.
The maximum health of the radio. If this value drops down to less than its corresponding regenerated health value, the signal distance will be reduced by 50 %.
The signal distance of the radio. Two friendly tank could see each other and the enemies they spotted if their distance is less than the sum of their radio signal distances.
The radius the HE shell explosion could affect.
The flying speed of the shell.
The gravity acceleration of the shell.
The maximum distance the shell could reach.

The piecing power of the shell. This value is represented by the piecing powers at 100m and 400m distance, between which the piecing power will reduce linearly. The value is randomly shifted by no more than 25 %.
The alpha damage of the shell. The value is randomly shifted by no more than 25 %.
The average damage could be dealt within one minute with the selected type of shell.
The damage of a shell could deal to modules and devices.
The price of a single shot.
Shell price divided by its alpha damage.
The factor applied to the piecing power of an HEAT shell, if it hits any (spaced) armour, its piecing power will be reduced by distance with this factor.
The maximum health of the surveying device. If this value drops down to less than its corresponding regenerated health value, the view range will be reduced by 50 %.
The maximum health of the tank.
The weight of all the equipment loaded.
The maximum repair cost of the tank.

The battle tiers to which this tank could encounter. A battle tier less than Ⅺ roughly equals to the highest tier of tanks which could appeared in its battle. Tier Ⅺ and Ⅻ battles has more tier Ⅹ tanks and less tier Ⅷ or Ⅸ tanks.
The price to buy this tank in stock configuration.

The percentage of view range negated to the enemy who is trying to spot you while you are stationary. This value is measured by tests, might be inaccurate. Mostly based on the test result of AndrasD and Devilhunter.

The percentage of view range negated to the enemy who is trying to spot you while you are moving. This value is measured by tests, might be inaccurate. Mostly based on the test result of AndrasD and Devilhunter.

The percentage of view range negated to the enemy who is trying to spot you while you are shooting in stationary. This value is measured by tests, might be inaccurate. Mostly based on the test result of AndrasD and Devilhunter.

The percentage of view range negated to the enemy who is trying to spot you while you are shooting and moving. This value is measured by tests, might be inaccurate. Mostly based on the test result of AndrasD and Devilhunter.
The matchmaking weight of the tank, reflects the tank's importance to the team considered by the matchmaking system.

The maximum health of the turret rotator. If this value drops down to less than its corresponding regenerated health value, the traverse speed of the turret will be reduced by 50 %. If this value reaches zero, the turret would get stuck and cannot traverse.
The maximum traverse speed of the turret.
The maximum view range of the tank.
The primary frontal armour of the turret.
The primary side armour of the turret.
The primary rear armour of the turret.
The horizontal traverse range of the turret.
The maximum health of the turret, which will be added up to the maximum health of the tank
Average damage dealt per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average damage received per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.

Average potential damage (from penetrated, non-penetrated and ricochet shoot) received per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average damage assisted per battle, by spotting enemy. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average damage assisted per battle, by destroying enemy tank's track. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Hit rate of this tank, with ricochets and unpenetrated shoots included. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average experience gained per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average net income per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average gross income per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average operation cost per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.

Average repair cost per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average mileage per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average enemy spotted (for the first time) per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Win rate of this tank. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average enemy damaged per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.

PA efficiency of this tank. PA efficiency is a modified version of the wot-news efficiency, used by vBAddict.net. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
WN7 efficiency of this tank. WN7 is generally considered the standard efficiency system. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.

WN8(D) efficiency of this tank. WN8 is a next generation efficiency system which is still in development. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
The battle capacity of this tank. Battle capacity is a variant of the XVM efficiency. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Based on data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average enemy killed per battle. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average battle time of this tank. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Survive rate of this tank. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Sample size of this tank. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Experience gained per minute. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Penetration rate of this tank. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Ricochet and unpenetration rate. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Percentage the tank was destroyed in the first minute and spotted any tanks. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Percentage the tank was not moved and did not dealt any damage. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.
Average battle tier encountered by this tank. This is a LiveStat which is based on random battles in the last 30 days. Data provided by vBAddict.net.

here are some basics about how to use Tank Inspector.
click the button below when you are ready.
The angle at which the test shell hits the target armour.
The angle to which the impact angle is adjusted towards the armour's normal axis. Only applicable for AP and APCR shells.
If the calibre of the shell is two times or more than the nominal thickness of the armour, the normalisation angle will be increased. Only applicable for AP and APCR shells.

If the calibre of the shell is three times or more than the nominal thickness of the armour, no ricochet will happen even if the impact angle is more than 70° from normal. Only applicable for AP and APCR shells.
AP Shell, with a standard normalisation angle of 5°
APCR Shell, with a standard normalisation angle of 2°

This setting will take effect at next time you launch Tank Inspector.
Select to show a random background image, otherwise the background will be left blank.
*press PRINTSCREEN in model view to take photo
The following options increases model graphics quality, but may impact performance. If Tank Inspector is running slowly, try to turn part or all of them off.
SSAO creates ambient-occluded shadings. This option could impact render performance, if Tank Inspector is running slowly, try to turn it off.
SMAA provides anti-aliasing for model rendering, making the model edges smoother. This option could impact render performance, if Tank Inspector is running slowly, try to turn it off.
Specularity simulates light reflection, making certain materials shiny. This option could impact render performance, if Tank Inspector is running slowly, try to turn it off.
Normal mapping enhances the appearance and details of models. This option could impact render performance, if Tank Inspector is running slowly, try to turn it off.
Anisotropic Filtering enhances texture image quality by eliminates aliasing effects. If Tank Inspector is running slowly, try to lower the filter level or turn it off.
Select to enable drawing strokes to separate different thickness of armours in collision model.
Select to use wireframe mode while rendering models.
Select to display how many frames are rendered within one second on the top-left of the model view.
Select to display how many triangles are there in the model being rendered on the top-left of the model view.
Select to display a crosshair while your mouse is over the model. This is useful if you want to figure out where the mouse is pointing to in your screenshot.
Use actual traverse speed for turret controller
The turret and gun will traverse in their actual speed while being manipulated with the turret controller, instead of changing their facing immediately.
Load elite configuration automatically for newly selected tanks.
Recruit new crews, instead of trying to retrain current crews by sustaining their training level and skills.
Newly recruited crews have 100% proficiency instead of 50%.
Reset reference tank to default benchmark tank
Reset reference tank to default benchmark tank, even if you have selected another tank as reference.
Reset to default ammunition type instead of trying to keep previously selected type.
Clear installed equipments instead of trying to reuse them.
Clear installed consumables instead of trying to reuse them.
Select to show description of data items in their tooltips.
Show as much stats as possible
Unimportant stats are defaultly collapsed in the data page. Enable this option to show as much stats as possible to fill up the data page.
